The paper deals with the problem of neuronal boundary detection in 3D electron microscopic brain images, which is a topic closely related to computer vision (cs.CV) and neural networks (cs.NE). The paper also discusses the use of deep learning techniques and backpropagation training, which are common in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper mentions the potential applicability of the proposed architecture to other types of anisotropic 3D images, including video, which falls under the category of multimedia (cs.MM).
